.TH "aaruremote" "1" "2026-06-05" "aaru-remote User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
\f[B]aaruremote\f[R] - remote server for Aaru, the disk imaging and
preservation software
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]aaruremote\f[R]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]aaruremote\f[R] is the server component of \f[B]Aaru\f[R], a disk
imaging and storage media preservation tool.
It receives commands sent by a remote Aaru instance, forwards them to a
local device, and returns the data back over TCP/IP.
.PP
The primary motivation for \f[B]aaruremote\f[R] is to provide access to
devices on machines that cannot run Aaru directly \[em] older systems,
architectures unsupported by .NET, or game consoles.
.PP
On startup, \f[B]aaruremote\f[R] prints the underlying operating system
version and the list of available IP addresses, then listens for
incoming connections on port \f[B]6666/TCP\f[R].
.PP
It accepts no command-line options.
.SS Privileges
.PP
\f[B]aaruremote\f[R] requires access to raw block devices.
When run manually, it should be executed as \f[B]root\f[R] to access
most device types (ATA, SCSI, NVMe, MMC/SD).
When managed by systemd, it runs as the dedicated \f[B]aaruremote\f[R]
user with supplementary groups \f[B]disk\f[R] and \f[B]cdrom\f[R], which
grants the necessary device permissions without requiring root.
.SS Supported device types
.PP
Depending on the platform, \f[B]aaruremote\f[R] supports the following
device types:
.TP
\f[B]ATA (CHS)\f[R]
ATA drives addressed in Cylinder/Head/Sector mode.
.TP
\f[B]ATA (LBA 28-bit)\f[R]
ATA drives with 28-bit logical block addressing.
.TP
\f[B]ATA (LBA 48-bit)\f[R]
ATA drives with extended 48-bit logical block addressing.
.TP
\f[B]ATAPI\f[R]
ATA optical drives (CD, DVD, Blu-ray).
.TP
\f[B]SCSI\f[R]
Generic SCSI devices, including optical drives and hard disks.
.TP
\f[B]NVMe\f[R]
NVMe solid-state drives.
.TP
\f[B]Secure Digital (SD)\f[R]
SD and SDHC memory cards.
.TP
\f[B]MultiMediaCard (MMC)\f[R]
MMC memory cards.
.SS Supported buses
.PP
Depending on the operating system, \f[B]aaruremote\f[R] can retrieve
bus-specific metadata for: \f[B]USB\f[R], \f[B]FireWire (IEEE
1394)\f[R], and \f[B]PCMCIA\f[R].
.SS Platform support
.PP
